The Anambra State Towns People Association has solicited the allocation of a park and recreation centre to the association for the promotion of the rich cultural heritage of the state and the country at large. Assistant President General of the association, Nze Kanayo Chukwumezie, who made the appeal during a meeting with the Director, Parks and Recreation of the FCTA, Hajia Raskatu Abdulazeez, in Abuja on Monday, also announced a partnership with the department under the Presidential Initiative Programme on Seed Planting. 